<p>Great tool &#8211; great idea! </p>
<p>I&#8217;m using a WinXP dev box and I wanted to advise that this tool blows up with stack trace starting like this:</p>
<p>couldn&#8217;t find HOME environment &#8212; expanding `~/.hoerc&#8217;<br />
c:/apps/ruby/lib/ruby/gems/1.8/gems/hoe-1.5.1/lib/hoe.rb:372:in `expand_path&#8217;<br />
c:/apps/ruby/lib/ruby/gems/1.8/gems/hoe-1.5.1/lib/hoe.rb:372:in `with_config&#8217;<br />
c:/apps/ruby/lib/ruby/gems/1.8/gems/hoe-1.5.1/lib/hoe.rb:408:in `define_tasks&#8217;<br />
c:/apps/ruby/lib/ruby/gems/1.8/gems/hoe-1.5.1/lib/hoe.rb:362:in `initialize&#8217;<br />
./config/hoe.rb:53:in `new&#8217;<br />
./config/hoe.rb:53</p>
<p>On Windows, there is no default HOME env var &#8211; once I stubbed one in there, things are working better. This may be a problem with hoe not newgem but I thought I should throw it out there.</p>
<p>Are you coming to RailsConf 2008 in Portland? I know it&#8217;s a long way. </p>
<p>Irregularly, S-</p>

